snippet.textDisplay:
It's hilarious how many braindead retards believe that Scarlett will be 4x more powerful than XBX. Those saying "24Tflops". I mean, okay, they don't know what is hardware, architecture, performance, they can't figure that Microshaft meant 4x CPU performance going from Bull2011dozer.

I mean, they don't understand that to power it you'd need a 600W+ PSU... which won't be conslow-sized. That you can't cool it with a vapor chamber or Intel's stock cooler. That such hardware would cost OVER A THOUSAND DOLLARS in PC parts.
Seriously, it can have 24Tflops. Totally. It will just cost 1000$, be a HUGE manufacturing at a loss, will be bought by maybe 5 people per city and and will require an extra layer of optimization compared to a standard 500$ online-only console. To even begin paying off the manufacturing costs - they'd need to slap a 20-30$ Premium Texture package onto every game.
